 18/8 /18 Herlevill not go too well on the front . Braithwait rang up that he could see A Coy come back and an appeal for assist came from Westaway . Present McCartin wound in three place rang up that A Co were not at the Crucifix and that he was in the air . Word now came that A Coy had been held up by M.G. fire and that Fulton and Evan were both wound . Young Smith rang up and told me how matter stood and old Holloway the runner also came in . On the left Westaway 's peopl seem to have been surround . Brazenor was kill ? so was Sgt Ellis of A Co. Armstrong , Westaway Mallinson are miss . The Boch was seen to march off
